          "en": "Use when budgeting the soil's nutrient capacity against crop demand — the N-P-K balance where a crop's nitrogen and potassium need (lbs/acre, as N and K₂O oxide forms) scales with its yield; heavy vs light feeders; legumes fixing their own nitrogen (N ≈ 0); the 4R stewardship and soil-test basis. Fertility is a double-entry budget: crop removal debits the soil, application credits it; it must balance like any ledger."
