          "en": "Use when output is spread across the season by staggered sequential sowings — succession planting: number of plantings (sowings) and number of harvests (pickings) are the two scheduling levers that replace one glut with a continuous supply. The interval between sowings ≈ one planting's picking window; total seasonal row-length divides evenly across the plantings to size each sowing and its seed order."
